    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to the pot over a low heat with a large splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Mash until smooth and stir through 2/3<strong> </strong>of the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>parsley mash</strong></p>",
